üó£Ô∏è GC: "I'd never been down this far before so it's been great to explore."

On January:

üó£Ô∏è GC: "We have to look at how we can get better. We are looking two or three windows in advance. Our process is clear and we know what we're looking for in terms of players."

#ECFC #OneGrecianGoal

Q for GC on previous managerial experiences:

üó£Ô∏è GC: "I became a manager at 32. I'm someone who believes in myself and I look back at being 32 and I knew very little. My journey to now has been a rollercoaster... The last 3 years has really prepared me for this opportunity." https://t.co/cBfG3sW04A

On the new training ground:

üó£Ô∏è GC: "I was taken aback by the size of the new building. This is a step the club have taken to drive standards and will be a brilliant environment for the players and staff to use. It will allow us to attract better players."

#ECFC #OneGrecianGoal https://t.co/h27c0Os65S

üó£Ô∏è GC: "I was really attracted to the fan ownership. The supporters are huge part of the club. This is a sustainable football club and it is my job to continue that with what I am given."

#ECFC #OneGrecianGoal https://t.co/1tprlfdzX4

üó£Ô∏è GC: "I'm a big believer in standards, and I'm a believer that the result is not the be all and end all. It is my job to drive standards."

#ECFC #OneGrecianGoal https://t.co/jkFuGPuuzo

üó£Ô∏è DP: "I've known Gary since Wigan and I didn't take much persuading when he asked me to join him.

"I'm enjoying the time away from the family! üòÇ"

üó£Ô∏è GC: "This is a unique football club that gives managers time and that is what attracted me to the job."

#ECFC #OneGrecianGoal

üó£Ô∏è GC: "I'm really thankful for the welcome I've had at Exeter. I'm loving the area, though it has rained every day since I arrived!"
